  "Alpha particles (⁴₂He) are large and heavily charged (+2), so they lose energy quickly when colliding with matter. A single sheet of paper — or even a few centimeters of air — is enough to stop them. Lead shielding and concrete walls are overkill for alphas (those are needed for gamma rays and neutrons). Aluminum centimeters would stop beta particles but are also unnecessary for alphas.": "",
