  "Inside the body, alpha particles deposit all their energy in a tiny area — causing tremendous local damage to DNA/tissues. External alpha is harmless (stopped by skin).": "",
  "The becquerel (Bq) is a unit measuring:": "",
  "Penetrating power": "",
  "Radiation dose absorbed": "",
  "Radiation energy in tissue": "",
  "Radioactivity (1 disintegration per second)": "",
